Trinijove helped 6000 young people threatened by the social exclusion
The organization was brought for the avoidance of the marginalization by young people without professional training into being.
The first 25 years of life of the social welfare assistance organization Trinijove led to important results: In this quarter century 6000 young people threatened by the social exclusion were supported, in order to find a way out of their difficult situation.
In addition the jobs created over hundreds for this social group come.
On the occasion of the anniversary with a meeting in the former work buildings by Fabra i Coats, in which over 300 persons participated, was pulled to balance yesterday.
Trinijove was brought 1986 in the city quarter Trinitat Vella with the goal into being, young people with small state of training, without work, with drug problems, which were threatened by the risk of the Marginalität to help.
In the celebration of yesterday in Sant Andreu participated numerous responsible person of facilities and institutions, which co-operated in these 25 years with the association.
The participation of political representatives of different directions at election campaign times occupied the impartiality of the work carried out by Trinijove.
Except the president of the Generali act (parliament of the autonomous region Catalonia), Artur Mas, and its predecessor Jordi Pujol Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and presently left-green town councillor Ricard Goma participated in the ceremonies the former socialist Secretary of Education.
Also the present katalonische Minister for social and family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the general manager of the social work of the savings bank La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa visited the large hall of Fabra i Coats.
Mas stressed that Trinijove in very difficult times was brought into being and that the today's times are not less complicated. But it added that the work carried out up to now is “a good basis”.
For the president of the Generali act Trinijove is a model, which knows to fight against difficult circumstances and hope gives humans in difficulties.
“The economic crisis is not anything new” for the association and the work, which it carries out, explained it.
